    HUD positioning rework: fixed offsets replacing peer-list stacker
    
    Removes the 250ms peer-list stacker that walked VS's dialog list and
    wrote to absOffsetY (an engine-owned field per the VS wiki). Replaces
    it with fixed per-anchor offsets applied via WithFixedAlignmentOffset
    (the documented knob). Storm HUD subscribes to Main's LayoutChanged
    event to re-stack below Main when they share an anchor.
    
    Key files:
      HudAnchorOffsets.cs   new; anchor -> Y-offset table, tunable constants
      MainHudView.cs        exposes CurrentLogicalOuterHeight
      MainHudController.cs  fires LayoutChanged; rebuilds on icon change
      MainHudViewModel.cs   HasVisibleIconChanged / MarkIconsBaked
      StormHudController.cs subscribes to LayoutChanged; sign-flips for
                            bottom anchors since WithFixedAlignmentOffset's
                            Y grows away from the anchor edge regardless
                            of side
      ClaimHudView.cs       uses ClaimBannerOffsetY from the shared table
    
    Offset values (verified at 4K / GUI scale 1.0):
      TopRight        260    clear minimap
      TopCenter       110    clear tooltip + claim banner
      BottomCenter   -150    sign flip + clear hotbar
      InterHudPadding  -5    tighten Main/Storm stacking
    
    Also fixes a pre-existing issue where the season icon and room-status
    icon never refreshed between settings-toggle Rebuilds: VS's
    AddStaticCustomDraw bakes the draw callback into the composer's
    cached texture at Compose time and doesn't re-run it. MainHudViewModel
    now tracks last-baked icon state; the controller's tick detects a
    change via HasVisibleIconChanged and triggers a full Rebuild instead
    of the text-only UpdateTexts fast path.
    
    Also bumps IconSize 100 -> 200 and refreshes the large season icon art.

